<script>
  window['_cpga'] = window['_cpga'] || {};
  _cpga.playedVideos = {};

  _cpga.videoIsFirstPlay = function (playerType, videoIdentifier) {
    return (typeof _cpga.playedVideos[playerType] === 'undefined' || _cpga.playedVideos[playerType][videoIdentifier] === -1);
  };

  _cpga.getVideoTimeViewed = function (playerType, videoIdentifier) {
    if (_cpga.playedVideos[playerType] && _cpga.playedVideos[playerType][videoIdentifier]) {
      return Math.round((Date.now() - _cpga.playedVideos[playerType][videoIdentifier]) / 1000);
    } else {
      return undefined;
    }
  };

  _cpga.resetVideoTimeViewed = function (playerType, videoIdentifier) {
    if (typeof _cpga.playedVideos[playerType] === 'undefined') {
      _cpga.playedVideos[playerType] = {};
    }

    _cpga.playedVideos[playerType][videoIdentifier] = Date.now();
  };
</script>

<script>
/**
  * Scroll tracking plugin for GTM
  * Description - this code was derived from the Google On Steroid plugin: https://github.com/CardinalPath/gas/blob/master/src/plugins/max_scroll.js
  * Author - Bill Tripple, btripple@cardinalpath.com
  * Version - 1.1
  * Implemented in template by: Dave Fimek
*/
(function(){
	var CP_ScrollTracking = (function () {
		/* configuration start */
		var SETTINGS={
			"scroll_grouping":{{CONS - Scroll Grouping}}, // 10(Deciles), 20(Quintiles), or 25(Quartiles) , needs to be changed in vars
			"data_layer_event_label":"e_scrollTracking",
			"data_layer_data_label":"scrollDepth"
		}
		/* configuration ends */
		
		var documentElement = document.documentElement;
		var _current_bucket=0
		var _max_scroll = 0;

		/**
		 * Get current browser viewpane height
		 *
		 * @return {number} height.
		 */
		function _get_window_height() {
			return window.innerHeight || documentElement.clientHeight ||
				document.body.clientHeight || 0;
		}

		/**
		 * Get current absolute window scroll position
		 *
		 * @return {number} YScroll.
		 */
		function _get_window_Yscroll() {
			return window.pageYOffset || document.body.scrollTop ||
				documentElement.scrollTop || 0;
		}

		/**
		 * Get current absolute document height
		 *
		 * @return {number} Current document height.
		 */
		function _get_doc_height() {
			return Math.max(
				document.body.scrollHeight || 0, documentElement.scrollHeight || 0,
				document.body.offsetHeight || 0, documentElement.offsetHeight || 0,
				document.body.clientHeight || 0, documentElement.clientHeight || 0
			);
		}

		/**
		 * Get current vertical scroll percentage
		 *
		 * @return {number} Current vertical scroll percentage.
		 */
		function _get_scroll_percentage() {
			return (
				(_get_window_Yscroll() + _get_window_height()) / _get_doc_height()
			) * 100;
		}
		
		function _update_scroll_percentage() {
			_max_scroll = Math.max(_get_scroll_percentage(), _max_scroll);
			var bucket = (_max_scroll > SETTINGS.scroll_grouping ? 1 : 0) * (Math.floor((_max_scroll) / SETTINGS.scroll_grouping) * SETTINGS.scroll_grouping);
			if(_max_scroll>95){bucket=100;} // close enough
			if(bucket>_current_bucket){
				//console.log("bucket"+bucket);
				_current_bucket=_max_scroll;
				if(bucket==100){
                    {{CJ - FN Remove Event Listener}}( window, "scroll", _update_scroll_percentage ) 
				}
				if (typeof(dataLayer) !== 'undefined') {
					var dL = new Object();
					dL["event"]=SETTINGS.data_layer_event_label;
					dL[SETTINGS.data_layer_data_label]=bucket;
					dataLayer.push(dL)
				}
			}
		}
		
		return{  // public interface
				init: function(){
                    {{CJ - FN Add Event Listener}}( window, "scroll", _update_scroll_percentage );
					return true;
				}
			}
	})();
	try{
		CP_ScrollTracking.init();
	}catch(ex){console.log(ex);}
})();
</script>

<script>
"use strict";

/**
  * Description - HTML5 Video Tracking, only works on browsers that support HTML5
  * Version - 1.0
*/
try {
	var lastP;
	var intervalId;
	var title;
	var html5Video;
	var i;

	(function () {
		var onProgress = function onProgress(e, title) {
			//console.log("in progress");
			intervalId = setInterval(function () {
				var duration = e.target.duration;
				var position = e.target.currentTime;
				var t = duration - position <= 1.5 ? 1 : (Math.floor(position / duration * 4) / 4).toFixed(2);
				if (!lastP[title] || t > lastP[title]) {
					lastP[title] = t;
					dataLayer.push({
						event: "e_video",
						videoAction: t * 100 + "% viewed",
						videoLabel: title,
						videoTimeViewed: _cpga.getVideoTimeViewed('html5', title)
					});
					_cpga.resetVideoTimeViewed('html5', title);
				}
			}, 200);
		};

		lastP = [];
		title = "";
		html5Video = document.getElementsByTagName("video");

		for (i = 0; i < html5Video.length; ++i) {
			title = html5Video[i].getElementsByTagName("source")[0].src;
			html5Video[i].onplay = function (e) {
				//console.log("in play");
				var pushObj = {
					event: "e_video",
					videoAction: "play",
					videoLabel: title
				};

				if (_cpga.videoIsFirstPlay('html5', title)) {
					pushObj.videoStart = 1;
					pushObj.videoDuration = e.target.duration;
				}

				dataLayer.push(pushObj);
				_cpga.resetVideoTimeViewed('html5', title);
				onProgress(e, title);
			};
			html5Video[i].onpause = function () {
				//console.log("in pause");
				dataLayer.push({
					event: "e_video",
					videoAction: "pause",
					videoLabel: title,
					videoTimeViewed: _cpga.getVideoTimeViewed('html5', title)
				});
				clearInterval(intervalId);
			};

			html5Video[i].onended = function () {
				clearInterval(intervalId);
			};
		}
	})();
} catch (ex) {}
</script>
